mistletoe 1.5.1. Let me look at the heart of `SaferWeblateHtmlRenderer.render_image` more closely. Notice the title attribute path:

```python
def render_image(self, token):
    if self.check_url(token.src):
        template = '<img src="{}" alt="{}"{} />'
        title = f' title="{html.escape(token.title)}"' if token.title else ""
        return template.format(self.escape_url(token.src), self.render_to_plain(token), title)
```

`token.title` is escaped. `self.escape_url(token.src)` escapes the URL. `render_to_plain` for alt. The `check_url` allows `/user/` and `https?://`. That looks ok.

Now the `convert_link` is interesting:
```python
def convert_link(self, link):
    return link.replace(' href="', ' rel="ugc" target="_blank" href="')
```

This is a string replace on already-rendered HTML. Let me check the `render_link` super in mistletoe 1.5.1 and how the URL/title are escaped. Let me find the mistletoe source.
